reviews: This place is loud, small, old and the pictures are nothing like the room we were given. It is tiny, yes, tiny by Paris standards. The beds are cheap and not comfortable. We hit our heads on the ceiling in 1/2 our room. We have stayed in many other Paris hotels and air bnbs and this one is terrible compared to others if similar prices.

Friendly Staff, Good location, but very noisy room, it is impossible to sleep , the street noise are very annoying, feel you are sitting in tne street.
We ask to chang our room but they expailn they are full and all rooms are like that.
I have no idea how other guests slept here and made a good review!

Safe box had problem, takes 1 hour to fix and eeveral time coming to room. Still not working correctly.

Very old facilities.

Not recommand , specially if you have problem with noise!

We were not expecting rooms to be overly large in Paris, but this “junior suite” is ridiculous! We are staying here for 5 days before moving on to Nice. We have full size luggage. Cannot move around the room without bumping into each other. Can’t use the tiny table and chairs-can’t get to them for luggage. Can only sit on the bed. Can’t turn around in the shower as it is so small and we are not big people. Can not imagine how small just a room is. That is why we upgraded to a suite hoping for more room. Hotel said there is no other room unless we want to pay even more.

The Suites/Hotel are in a great location, just a road or so over from the Champs Elysee. The main sites all within walking distance, or in our case not far from one of the main pick up points for the hop on hop off bus routes.

The rooms were self contained, clean and comfortable. We were high up so even had a view of the top of the EIffel Tower from the read balcony.

Expensive, but that's central paris.

Location is ideal for red bus tours and also close to Arc de triomphe. Rooms are quite small but comfortable and clean. Modern interior. Rooms have a mini bar and nespresso machine. Staff at hotel very friendly and helpful. Will definitely return.

Very nice hotel just a short walk from the champs-elysees.
Friendly staff on check in, room had everything I needed for the short stay.
Great value
Rooms well equipped and clean
Would definitely use this Hotel again.

This was a very comfortable and cosy hotel within walking distance to some of the main icons of Paris including the Eiffel Tower and the Arc De Triomph.

The staff are professional and friendly, and very welcoming. We got the family room which was ideal for the 4 of us.

We have booked 2 suites for a family trip to Paris. The hotel’s location is perfect, walking distance to Champs Elysees. However, the suites are a joke in comparison to their prices. With those prices we expected to have a comfortable stay but sadly we didn't. As a regular tourist in Paris I have stayed in many hotels around Champs Elysees with much lower prices and better rooms.
Strangely enough, you’ll be charged for the water bottles and Nespresso capsules in the room.

clean, modern and friendly staff right in the middle of town
would stay again anytime

I left my headphones in the room, and the staff posted them to Australia for me no issues

Well recommended
thank you

Very nice hotel and very close to the Arc De Triomphe. My wife, two daughters and I visited at the beginning of August 2022 and stayed for 3 nights.

We had a one bedroom suite, the kids slept in the salon on a fold out bed. The suite is fully equipped for self catering including a well stocked mini bar. As a family of four (My daughters are both young teenagers) it was a tiny bit cramped, but we were out most of the time. One doesn’t visit Paris to hang around a hotel.

Staff were all lovely, nothing too much trouble. Even borrowing a plug adaptor for us from a neighbouring hotel when we forgot to bring ours.

Close to the Champs Ellyses, the metro and a monoprix. Perfect for a trip to one of the nicest cities in the world

This hotel suite was very nice, clean and cozy. The front desk was so helpful in arranging our transport to the airport and they were also accommodating on allowing us to check in a little early. The room we had was a mini studio it was very small but perfect for 2 people. I would definitely stay here again.

Nice hotel, great people and superb location! I lost my e-reader on my bed when I left, and the staff was super friendly and send it back to me to the Netherlands. Would really recommend booking here when visiting Paris.

We were a family of 2 adults and 2 teens. This hotel suited us perfectly. Location is fantastic near all main sites and suite had 2 rooms, one with sofa bed, small kitchen and lounge area. Would def recommend

Great location for tourists and 5 minutes from metro. Lots of high-end (expensive) shops. Amazing restaurants, one a few doors away. Very friendly & helpful staff. Clean & cozy room. Great communication before, during and after stay. Comfortable bed but pillows too soft. Would stay again! Recommended.

Spotlessly clean hotel. Staff very polite and friendly. Room cleaned daily. Downside, coffee/tea/milk chargeable.
On a main road so slight road traffic if your in one of the front rooms and a light sleeper.
WiFi good, no bar area for a chill
Great location

Excellent location, very friendly and helpful staff and brilliant value for money. Perfect for a few days exploring Paris. Very highly recommended.
Отлично местоположение, любезен персонал и добро съотношение цена-качество. Перфектен за няколкодневен престой в Париж.

Perfect solution in the center of Paris.
Very clean and cute room.
Staff kindness and support has been simply perfect.
I recommend it for a buisness trip but also for a weekend holiday.
Tatally recommended.

Great location friendly staff and helpful
Kind of compact for two with one bed but very clean and comfortable. Would definitely stay again when visiting Paris
You are able to open windows if too warm as well

The apartments are small but for a stay in the middle of Paris it was great. The apartment was functional and quiet, with transport very close by. Would definitely recommend. Staff were friendly and they made an exception for our very late check in, so thank you for that

The location of the hotel is excellent. The staff was very nice and the rooms wel very clean. I would highly recomend this hotel if you want to stay near the champ elysee and the shops. Thank you for the service!

My stay at the Helzear was very comfortable and welcoming. Mariem made sure my family was in good care while we visited Paris. The breakfast that is served is very good as well. The location of the hotel is superb. Will recommend to friends and family.

I struggle a little buy think 3* is a reasonable overall rating.

First the good:
- Excellent location near Champs Elysee. The George V station and shopping street is literally a 5min walk away. You can also walk lightly to the Arc de Triomphe and Eiffel Tower from here
- Professional staff. They are not exactly knowledgeable, but they will smile and say hi when you pass the lobby.
- Room cleaning service was excellent.
- There are basic cooking amenities like microwave, stove, kettle and utensils.

What’s missing:
- Names of room types are inflated, and images don’t show the room accurately. As such you can’t really tell accurately what you are booking. Our room was one bedroom suite, which was actually a tiny room with a loft for a “bedroom”.
- Room layout was incredibly tight. Once the sofa bed was set, you’d literally need to climb over the bed to get to the bathroom. You need to crawl into the loft bedroom because there is no standing space.
- Ceiling and floorboards were very thin. There was one night we had a family above which dragged furnitures late into the night and talked loudly, and we could hear them well. That said the reception did try to help to talk to them.

On hindsight we would have booked something bigger for our family of four. But I think they could have more clearly represented what the rooms actually are like on their website and on the booking engines, so we can make a more accurate booking. And the “suite room” layout that hinders access to the bathroom is really mind-boggling.

My boyfriend and I stayed at this hotel for 3 nights as a treat for our 9 year anniversary. We were absolutely delighted that the staff at the hotel gave us a room with a fantastic street view and a complimentary breakfast. It was absolutely amazing! The room itself was spacious and immaculate, the bathroom & shower so nice. Every single staff member we spoke to was polite, friendly and really helpful. The cleaners were also super lovely and left our room completely spotless. We will definitely be back! Thank you so much for an unforgettable stay in Paris.

Decent room and good location.
Room did suffer from small amount of road noise. It didn’t both us but if you’re a light sleeper then may be not good. Biggest disappointment is that my pre-authorisation monies from check-in have not been returned 3 weeks after returning. I have had to chase this 3 times and still no success. Having read other reviews this seems to be a common theme and one which the business should address sooner rather than later should they want repeat business.

The hotel was very well located - parallel to Champs Elysees. There is a lift in the hotel - good for those with rooms on upper floors, with luggage. Unfortunately, we were allotted the room on the ground floor located right next to the street - and we could hear traffic noise or people walking by talking/laughing along the street. Thankfully it isn't a major road, so traffic was not so heavy or noisy. Also people entering/leaving the hotel for check in, etc. We requested for a room change and the hotel staff was very nice and accommodating - they agreed to move us if there were any other available rooms. Unfortunately, there weren't any. But the hotel offered us free breakfast the next day - it was a nice gesture. We stayed there for 3 nights - after the 1st night we got used to the noise, and it became more like background noise. Our friends booked another room in the hotel - it was located on the 2nd floor, very well placed, so quiet. So overall, the hotel was a good one, and I would recommend staying there!

great friendly staff, near to Champs Elysee, Etoile, Seine and Metro, loved to stay there for my culturall trip with visit at Opera Bastille, Theatre de Champs Elysee, Louvre, Le Marais, Bois de Bouelogne and so on

Honestly it was An amazing experience. The service was great , the people who work here are all nice and helpful the rooms are spacious and overall very nice and most importantly the location is outstanding it’s just walking distance from the most important street here in Paris the champs Élysée

I wanted to stay close to the Arc de Triomphe in Paris and this hotel came up during my search. I booked the Junior Suite in the 6th floor. I loved the cleanliness and modern design. The nespresso machine unfortunately was broken and I wish there would have been more Nuxe products to sample in the bathroom. There was personal note in the room however it would have been nice to be addressed as Ms rather than Mr. There is a lovely boulngerie close to the hotel so I could have a lovely breakfast on the balcony. I’d love to visit again. I would have preferred if staff had encouraged mask wearing as several hotel guest walked around without a mask.

Very nice suite kind of accommodation with kitchenette . has expresso machine, stove and microwave shower is a bit small but bathroom is adequate, great location.
Close to arc de triomphe and champs Elysees.
very helpful receptionists.

Very clean and beautiful apartment. Staff very friendly and helpful . It is located in a good area central- but not noisy. It has a fully equipped kitchen so I would recommend it for family with little kids .

The best thing this hotel offers is the location. It's a 5-minute walk to one of the most touristy streets in Paris, the Champs-Élysées. The morning staff is helpful, but the night staff was useless. There was a plumbing issue one night that resulted in no water for any of the rooms, and instead of offering us a discount for that night, they left a gift in the room of hygiene products. Despite numerous attempts to follow up with the hotel director, no attempt to contact us was made. The room itself was much smaller than what the photos make it out to appear, and you can hear nearly sound made in the hallways.

The stuff is helpful and eager to get the guest satisfaction. The place is clean. Very excellent location. The rooms a bit small but it’s exactly as written in the description at Booking.com. Overall I highly recommend staying at this hotel

very clean rooms, helpful, nice and professional receptionist, unfortunately a paving on a street and that means that you can't open window for night or use earplugs... thet is the only one minus, great location.

Really enjoyed my experience during my short stay nearby the most beautiful avenue Champs Élysées. Beds and helpful staff always caring and asking if everything is going well. I will surely stay again 🤝

I have stayed in the hotel on four occasions now, simply as it is so convenient. I have done all that is possible to build a relationship with the hotel myself but the management remain hard to reach which is odd as a returning guest. Separately the reception staff are most kind, Khalil and Meriem especially. My room was spotless, though I would appreciate a phone that worked. I will return on the condition that a member of the management greet me personally, which I think it acceptable in such cirumstances.

Location very very convenient.

The hotel has two locations; due to Cover-19 the hotel for which I had a reservation was closed. I was sent an e-mail twenty minutes before my expected arrival; did not receive it as I was traveling from the airport; went to the first address: nothing. Called the hotel and was directed to the second address. Rooms and amenities were of a much lower standard than expected from the photos of the first location. What was advertised as a Junior Suite was below standard. Only some of the toiletries were individually wrapped. The staff were professional and apologetic, but the hotel still sent my booking agent an incorrect ¨no show¨message. This location was not at all a 4Star venue; perhaps the original location measures up to that standard.

I highly recommend this place. My favourite recently.
Nice staff, clean and very nice location.
The staff os very helpful.
The decoration is really nice and stylish.
I will definitely go back on my next trip.

The service here really made our holiday. The staff were friendly and helped us find great spots for food and entertainment in the area. The hotel was clean, well decorated and in a great location too.

The Hotel Helzear Champs saved our vacation! We planned a family trip to the 2019 Women’s World Cup in Paris several months in advance. With just five days before our departure, an AirB&B owner cancelled our reservation (seems he was able to get more $$ for the apartment since it was World Cup month and Fashion Show week.) We scrambled to find a place that could accommodate six people during one of the the busiest months in Paris. This hotel was a lucky find. The staff was great and the location was excellent. My daughter and I stayed in a tiny room but that’s to be expected in Europe. My parents had a room with a outdoor balcony and we spent most several nights drinking wine outside. Overall, we walked everywhere from this great location. The hotel is air conditioned and the beds were comfy. The Champs has a sister hotel nearby that looks slightly larger and nice outdoor patio for coffee. Booking th is hotel literally saved our trip! Women’s soccer was amazing and Helzear was a great home base for games.

We stayed overnight before leaving for a pilgrimage to Fatima,Portugal . Our room was Balzac on the ground floor. It was a very good space for me and my husband.The staff - Servane and Keba were so nice . had to ask them if we could leave our luggage as we are going to Fatima for 4 days and be back again for an overnight stay.Was back after 4 days and our luggages were intact in there storage room. we were given a room upstair and the room was so cramped for our luggages and can't fully open the cabinet beside the bed. Had to request for change of room and Mariem was so nice to help us get back to our Balzac room downstairs even helping us pull our luggages to the tiny elevator. The room was clean, bed comfy , towels are clean, though shower drain was not that fast but manageable.Had the same shuttle/driver to bring us to CGD .Location was great for shopping , eating and sight seeing.

Helzear is the Best Hotel i have ever stayed at Champ Elysees:-esp the New York room-nice modern interior& clean with a nice balcony&very classic antiqu elevator &very close to champ elysees&Arc de Triomphe(i got a chance to jog wif my neph)Awesome!&the very best part is the Helzear staffs are very friendly&very helpful(sent my Nintendo Switch charger all the way from Champ Elysees to K.L Malaysia)Love you guys!

I recently returned from a trip around Europe. Paris was the final stop on our travels and our final days were perfect. Helzear was clean, comfortable and in a good location. The service was excellent, with a rotating cast of consistently kind and personable receptionists and cleaners. The taxi which the hotel ordered for us was actually the best taxi I have ever been in for my entire life. I hope to return one day!

I stayed with my family for a single night in a two bedroom apartment at the Hotel Helzear Champs-Elysees back in December, in the midst of the transportation strike. All in all we had a great experience, and my complaints are all minor. Still, I would really give it 4 - 4 1/2 stars, but I’m raising the rating to 5 because of the service by staff.

The apartment itself is what I’ve seen described in books as an ‘efficiency apartment “. It’s designed to take best advantage of the reduced space. In general it succeeded, but there were a couple of misses.

The two bedrooms were very small, just large enough to accommodate the double beds. This meant no room for night stands, but also nowhere to put your glasses. Adding a shelf would be helpful. The beds were comfortable enough- though as it was the case with all the hotel beds we experienced during this trip to Europe and the Middle East - too hard for our American expectations. Ditto for the pillows. One of my daughters slept in the sofa bed, and she had no complaints.

The bathroom was small, but well designed and we appreciated the towel warmer (which seems de rigeur for hotels in continental Europe). They had very nice toiletries and good water pressure.

The living room and kitchen were a bit cramped, but we didn’t have much need of them given our short stay. I did appreciate that they had a minibar, with prices not as ridiculous as in chain hotels.

My main quibble is that the apartment lacked any personality or style. I was hoping for something that had the basic charm of the rooms pictured here, but there was nothing of the sort. Inside the apartment, there was no sense we were in Paris, as opposed to anywhere else. Of course, this is ultimately on me for not researching it better.

The hotel location is wonderful, very close to the Metro line 1, which is automated and therefore was running normally during the strike. We were able to take it to the Louvre. The hotel itself is a little hard to find, however. There is only a small sign next to the door, and our taxi driver missed it. They also need to buzz you in to enter, which can be annoying. Elevators require a key card, if I remember correctly, and they are tiny.

What made my experience 5-star was the service from the staff at the Helzear, in particular the female receptionist in the morning we left (I wish I remembered her name). After the taxi company she called for us to take us to the airport flaked on us, she used her personal account to call an Uber for us. When we ended up canceling it, I compensated her for the expected cancellation fee, but she chased my taxi and ended up returning it because Uber didn’t charge it.

All in all, this is a great place to stay in Paris, as long as you are not expecting old world charm in your apartment decor.

The place is very nice and clean with a cute kitchen.All the staffs were very nice and helpful. Perfect for a get away in Paris.5 minutes from metro station.I highly recommend it over any big name hotel.

Excellent service. All the service staff are all time offering different type of help. I should mention the name of Mr. Hassan who was so helpful that makes our travel at Paris so easy. The location is very convenient to travel any direction of Paris city. I enjoyed my stay at the hotel. Cleanliness inside and outside room I found always up to the mark.

Excellent location in Paris ,central for all the sights , nice room good view on street clean and good front of house service. Would return again if visiting the city.
Shared a suite with sofa bed , not huge rooms but space enough for 3 people

this Hotel had made my stay very satisfying. Everything was on point and the staffs are so kind, helpful and very welcoming. This is one of the best hotels I have ever stayed in. I would definitely come back for another stay very soon. Keep up the great work.
Simply amazing

I stayed two nights at this apartment hotel for business trip. The first night was in a junior suite which located on the first floor with all windows directly facing the main street. Because the windows are big and very thin and the street is busy with cars all the time, I can hear all the noises from the street and cannot sleep during the night. It’s as noisy as if you were directly sleep on the street... It was really bad, especially I had a meeting the next day. I wouldn’t consider the junior suite it’s suitable for business stay. For the room structure, it is like a loft. You need to walk up the staircases to your bed, which is on an add-in floor with very low ceiling. Besides, the bed is not a real bed, it’s just a 20cm mattress and you can only sit but not stand in that space in order to not hit your head.

Another bad part is the taxi booking service: they helped me reserved a taxi at early morning to the airport and I confirmed with them that the taxi will drive directly to the airport without picking up other passengers in between. Apparently that is not the case! First of all, the driver is 30min late to pick me up, and then, she drives around the block in the bad Paris morning traffic to pick up another client (who goes to a different terminal than me) from the same hotel chain of Helzear, as the driver said it is arranged by the hotel like this. It made the time arriving the airport very tight. What surprised me the most is: each of us needs to pay the full price of the taxi! That’s was totally not communicated before.

Overall I will not consider again this hotel for my other trips to Paris.

This hotel offers easy walking distance to the Eiffel Tower and also to the Arc de Triomphe and Avenue des Champs-Élysées. Our suite was comfortable while clean and well maintained. The service staff including Albane and Massi were very helpful in meeting our requests and assisting with travel questions.

I booked a junior suite from booking.com when I checked in I was asked to pay the full amount then when I went put to room I found a tiny room not a junior suite by any means with a small bed against the wall that can't fit 2 people. I went back to the reception to ask them to change my room they told me that they were full for the nigth and they will change it in the morning.
The next day they refused to change the room or refund my money so I can go to another hotel. The pictures you see are not true and this hotel IS NOT A 4 STARS.

Ive stayed at the Helzear many times and each time they somehow manage to make it better. The staff are fantastic and really look after your every need. On my last to visits Ines has been fantastic. Thank you Ines for your attention and welcome.
I will be back there again soon.

Very small, but most places in Paris are. The staff was helpful and took us to our rooms and showed us around. Located within walking distance to the Arc de Triumph. No real sites to see from our particular rooms, but that wasn’t why we stayed there, so it was fine. Elevator was extremely small, but it was a nice addition that a Parisian hotel had a an elevator in general, so I wasn’t complaining. They held our bags upon checkout until our shuttle to the airport arrived later that evening.

Situated in a neighborhood that will provide you the perfect Paris experience you're looking for. Particularly want to highlight my experience with the front desk concierge, Ines. She was so lovely and helpful. Her hospitality made our stay even more enjoyable.

Great for long stays because they have a kitchenette in their rooms. Room is a bit crammed for 2 adults and 2 children with 3 big luggage. There’s a laundry shop, a small grocer, and lots of places to eat nearby. No breakfast provided but there are numerous cafes within 2 minutes walk that open around 8 or 9am. Around 15 minutes walk to Arch de triomphe and 10 minutes walk to Champs Elysses.

Lovely hotel for our 2 night stay. The small kitchen was a huge plus for us especially when preparing food for the kids exploring Paris. Supermarket close by was also an advantage. Thanks to Ines at front desk who went above and beyond, will be back.

We visited paris in july and our stay at this hotel was great. Location is great very close to Champs Elysis amd very close to Eiffel tower as well. Special thanks to Inez for being such a lovely host at the hotel. She was very helpful in anything that we needed. She even let my wife borrow her personal hair straightening iron. Overall a nice hotel with great customer service and location! Highly recommend

This is a small, boutique hotel that is in a perfect area for seeing Paris. Just a few minutes from the Champs Elysees and the Arc de Triomphe (closest Metro stop) and on a quiet street. The staff are wonderful to deal with and were very quick to reply to email messages. They arranged for someone to pick us up at the airport and it was seamless. Our room was on the main floor/street level but was actually a large size room (with a pull out sofa) with an efficiency and seating area. Staff was extremely accommodating and friendly - Ines in particular was lovely to deal with! Would definitely recommend.

I spent three nights at Helzear Champs-Elysées. I travel a lot but believe I have rarely seen such a disastrous price-quality ratio. About 400 € per night for a rather small room, facing the street and poorly soundproofed without any chairs (two bad iron stools - I asked for at least one chair because I have back problems, I was given one evening for one evening which was then taken back. Small bathroom (without bathtub and without any shelf to place toiletries). And annoying little things: nothing to put a suitcase somewhere else than on the ground; box of kleenex... empty. The staff is rather nice but not necessarily competent: no waking up in the morning as requested and a barely polite note on my pillow telling me not to smoke anymore while I'm not smoking... Why not the lowest grade? clean room and not ugly. But still: better to avoid!

We stayed in the 2 bedroom apartment. The beds were comfortable. The apartment is small but we expected that in Paris. The staff was friendly. Would definitely stay there again. Close to everything we wanted to do in Paris!

Just left the hotel with my parents after staying 3 days and I strongly feel that I have to write and thank for the amazing service. The location is so well, so convenient and so close to everywhere for a short visit in Paris. Our room was perfect; clean and cozy. We were only minutes away from the beautiful centre of Paris.
Above all is the people working in this beautiful hotel! Every one of them were utterly helpful, sincerely friendly and all smiles. A very special thanks to Yasen who welcomed us at the check in and eased and arranged everything for us at the check out as well; you are an amazing person and hope you to be very successful in your life! We are so lucky to run into such beautiful people in a short time; a very big thank to all of you guys!

Stayed here for 4 nights, service was very good and staff were very friendly, especially Mariam and Ines. The rooms were clean and the location was convenient, close to the metro and major attractions.

Ines was the most amazing and accommodating person we could have ever run into in Paris. She made all our requests come true with the greatest of ease . Everyone should have an Ines in their lives
Merci Inez

Great location in Paris, close to both Eiffel Tower and Arc De Triomphe. Additionally, it is less than 5 minutes of walking away from the Champs Elysees. Ines was a great help during the checkout process!

Cozy, close to everything, and the staff, particularly Inez, was amazing, helping with directions, transportation, and recommendations. This hotel is really close to great landmarks, shopping, but is still a restful haven. This hotel has my strong endorsement.

Not long ago I was in París, France. París is a place that I love and I like so much been there. I like it because it was the first time I was in París and it was a new experience, because we went with the school. My classmates and I stay in a hotel with the teachers. We always went to a new place to eat and that was very cool, because the food was very good. I also like the food in Paris because there were a lot of types that I never try. All the days we take a public transport and I have to say that the transports in París, are very clean and news. We use a bus that had TV and a train very beautiful and clean. I really like the transports there. In París we did a lot of things like go to see museums, visit famous places and many activities more. In my opinion, París was the best trip of my life.

We booked Deluxe 1 bedroom suite and Orbitz had it as courtyard view but when we got our room, the room was facing Avenue Marceau (very noisy every morning from 6:30am-8:30am). We have contacted hotel 3-4 times requesting courtyard view room for our reservation but no response at all from hotel. Orbitz had free breakfast included in our reservation but staffs told us breakfast would be €12. Very big discrepancy between what the hotel told us and what Orbitz had on their website. Staffs were very nice. Location is in the middle of Paris. About 5-10 minutes to Eiffel Tower, Champs Elysse, Laurdee (macaroons shop), Arc de Triompe, shopping, restaurants, and bus stops.
No taxi can go in or out of the area on Saturday due to yellow jacket protest.

We were amazing welcomed by Ines at the suites. The workstaff were so nice!! The location is perfect for the shoppers! It is 3 minutes from the champs elysees and we enjoyed our stay in the beautiful suit! Must stay here!!!

The service was great. Ines was very hospitable and we felt really welcome. She also gave us great tips about Paris and how to deal with pickpockets. She even welcomed us in Chinese!!!! How great.
The hotel has a great Paris vibe. Very recommended and would definitely come again.

Very warm staff specially Inés always helping or reconmending times, taxis,
very well located close to champ elysees, Arc the Triumph, easy to go to tour eiffel. The rooms very comfortables with small kitchen

We hit a home run when we chose this spot for our first two nights in Paris. The welcome we received from Ines was the warmest by far of any place we stayed during our Paris adventure. She made sure we understood this was a home for us while in the city and was so kind and helpful to this pack of very tired Americans, bleary eyed and just off an overnight flight. Our suite was great and nicely sized for the four of us — including my husband and son, who are both 6’ tall (and who often feel cramped when we all share quarters). Good shower, good kitchenette. This hotel is in a perfect location for sightseeing, an easy walk to the Metro, and tons of places to get food and drink are nearby. (Do not miss the views from the top of the nearby Arc de Triomphe. Absolutely the best views of Paris.) Would not hesitate to stay here again!

My mother and I really loved our stay in this hotel! It's in a great location, the rooms are modern, and there is a kitchenette that is well equipped. There is also an accessible room which was great to see ! However, most of these 5 stars belong to the amazing Ines and her wonderful service ! My mother and I were a bit anxious as we miscalculated the time needed to get to the airport. Ines acted quickly by arranging for the next available taxi driver to rush over and pick us up. While we waited for the taxi, Ines was able to keep us calm and relaxed. She made the situation less stressful, and I truly think she has a unique gift when it comes to interacting with people. When the taxi arrived, she explained the urgency of the situation and we were able to make our flight (shout out to the taxi driver for Helzear as well, he was also a great individual ! ). Overall, this is a great hotel not only because of the location and rooms, but also because of staff (like Ines) who really go above and beyond ! Thank you, Ines !

Very well located. Super cute and friendly staff. Special shoutout to dynamic and kind Ines who welcomed us with a big smile and a big heart! Loved the trendy deco and the books at every step. I highly recommend the executive suite and the junior suite 😍

i have read the comments before that i reserve and honestely it's not at all fair .all people are taking about the room size if you are real travelers you will know that this is the case in all paris hotel and only the hotel with rate room 1000€ you can have real space .for people hwo are looking for honest opinion , i give this hotel a service of a palace only because the girl at the reception that i will never forget her name she is amazing in every thing very natural she let me feel at home and she realy care about her guest not only me ,if you need any service just ask for ines and yes ines i believe you you have the magic stick i forgot all the problems i have with her wonderful smile and positive sprit i will advice all my friends and familly your hotel and for sure i will be back again .but only in the hotel in wich you are working .thx for her manager sofiane i just saw him few seconds but i understand that all the staff are wonderful .thx ines again for all your advice you are so pretty ,lovely ,smiling and you do more that you have to do

Ines is great! Very Friendly and made us feel right at home. She gave us a lot of recommendations on places to eat around the area. She did not hesitate to let us know that they are there to answer any questions that we may have. First impression is key to us and she delivered on a great first impression. The room that we were given is a great size for us! We are looking forward to a great stay.

i just over night in this hotel
helzear marceau , and have surprise about the services ( i sware ) also the people specialy lady in the front wdesk wich name Ines . she let me feel like im home also spare time fore to check out because iam shopping many so i confuse to pack my staff so thx for ines who save my day and my time and we will back again with our daughter and chlildren

The hotel location is excellent and room is clean and the staff (Einas) was very friendly and the hospitality was Great the bathroom is clean and the coffee machine is very nice and we will come back to that hotel

As a couple, we stayed over for 2 days, booked a ‘studio’.... well clearly it was just a bedroom with a small kitchen counter and an en-suite bathroom.
You can barely change your mind in the space it’s so small. For 2 people, it’s ok if you coming to sleep and out all day. But for the price you pay for a ‘studio’..... there are definitely bigger places for the same price close by.Great location and the reception staff are helpful, however it is small if booking a room or studio. The shower you can barely move in it, so don’t drop the soap!

Big thanks to Ines and the manager, Sofiane!
Not only they made me feel welcome as this was my first place I headed upon arrival in Paris, but I had some personal issues and they were really considerate and helped me out! I cannot thank them enough. Thanks for making my stay a super pleasant one!

Very good one, the best cost benefit ! The location is fantastic. Ines ( in the reception ) was great and made things even better !!! Many thanks to all there , totally recommend

The furniture is new and although some rooms are small the stay was very comfort for my family ( me , my wife and two young children )

Stayed here in December 2018 for two nights. Had a first floor room looking over the street, we got quite a bit of street noise coming through the window which wasn't ideal. The room is small with a pillar in the middle of it but is quite nice. The room also has kitchen facilities plus there is a room service menu. It is quite confusing when you arrive at the hotel though, with the door at the front not opening for anyone so you have to wait for a staff member to notice you. The lift is also incredibly small but it's just the nature of the old French building. Location is great close to everywhere you need to go in Paris. No English Channel on the TV also. All up, great room facilities and a pleasant stay.

I think it's fair to say they ROBBED me. Be careful with your CREDIT CARD with this hotel. I stayed there for two nights early Sept 2018 and I had paid for my rooms through a booking site already. Then after check-out, I noticed that they charged my credit card again for one of the nights. I thought it was a mistake so I contacted them. At first they replied back saying they'll give me full refund. They said it's impossible to cancel the credit card transaction, and said they'd send it via bank transfer. But they didn't refund me for over 2 months and ignored at least 10 of my emails so far. They rarely answer their calls and avoids the conversation saying they don't speak English or the person in charge is not there. Then a few days ago, they charged me AGAIN for the city tax and water bottle I had paid for at check-out. Seriously?! After 2 months????? There needs to be a serious change in their management, it not, this hotel should not be in hotel business. I WANT MY REFUND AND PROPER APOLOGY.

Modern hotel with great facilities. We stayed for only one night with a party of 5 people in a 2 x double bedroom apartment with a sofa bed. Reception staff was friendly and professional. The room we stayed in on the top floor was very quiet despite the central location, situated a 5-minute walk from the Arc de Triomphe. Highly recommended for families looking for reasonably priced accommodation in central Paris. Lots of nearby eating locations are also available.

Best of all the accomodation we stayed in on our three week Europe trip. Reasonably priced and close to everything. The staff went above and beyond many times and really helped when we thought we had lost our credit cards!

We stayed at Helzear Champs Elysees for 5 nights at the end of September. We had the Junior Suite.
We were disappointed with the accomodation as a whole and will not recommend anyone to stay there.
Prior to our stay but after booking, we called the hotel roughly 4 times. On each attempt, there was no response. Upon arrival we noticed that when a call came, they would answer and immediately hang up the phone. Staff were not helpful when asked questions about tourism.
The check in time which was on the booking stated 1pm, to which they said it was a mistake and to come back at 3pm. Thus, after a 21 hour flight we had to sit down the road with our bags and wait for 2 hours. We also had been advised when booking that we would have a balcony and a private terrace, but in fact we had no balcony or terrace. When asked, the staff again said that it must be a mistake. No effort was made to rectify this.
The apartment itself was small, old and the air conditioning was inconsistent.

The only positive to our stay at this hotel was the location. If travelling again though, this would be last on the list.

My family of 5 had a great stay at this Helzear Champs-Elysees recently. We had a two bedroom apartment facing onto the Avenue Marceau. It was a beautiful outlook and a great location. We could walk to the Eiffel Tower, Arc de Triumph, Champs-Elysee, and George V Metro station which is on Line 1 was 5 minute walk. There are great restaurants around as well as supermarket, cafes, laundromat, patisseries and even a lovely florist not far away. We really felt like we were in the centre of Paris - which we were! The staff were very nice and helpful. Special mention to Khalil who went out of his way to make us feel welcome. The main bedroom was large although the second bedroom and living space were not (typical in Paris) especially when the sofa bed is used, BUT as a family of 2 adults and 3 children were had ample space. The rooms were clean, plenty of storage, lovely modern bathrooms, and beautiful large windows! We will definitely stay here again!!

We stayed here for 2 nights over a weekend for a girl’s trip to Paris. It was ideally located off the George V road and convenient for the metro. There were cafés, corner shops and patisseries close by which again were ideal to bring some vino back to our room. Not to mention the fabulous Champs Elyse!!
There were 4 of us in an apartment which had a mezzanine bedroom plus a settee in the living room which turned into a bed. The only downside was only 1 bathroom (and mirror!) which can be an issue for 4 women sharing 
The reception staff were friendly and welcoming.
The room was clean and well kept.
The beds comfortable, including the settee bed which was very easy to pull out and in.
The location was fantastic
What more could you want.

Perfect location, warm welcome, great friendly local knowledge and lovely room. The bed was super comfortable, room was plenty big enough and the bathroom/shower was great. Highly recommend to anyone looking for a place very close to Eiffel tower, Arc De Triumph and the Champs-Élysées. The only part that could've been better was having someone at the desk more often, there was many times there was no one at the desk for assistance. The staff happily stored our bags for us and organised a taxi for us on our departure day. Loved our visit!

We stayed at the Helzear Suites from 31st August until 3rd September and had the best time. The hotel is perfectly located with Hermes on the corner as you enter the street (Christopher Columbus) and the Arc De Triomphe in view on the other side (Avenue Marceau). It’s ideal for visiting Paris and you can easily reach all of the main attractions without any hassle. There are plenty of shops, bars and restaurants around the area and lots of choice in terms of cuisine.

Our room was actually in the hotel on Avenue Marceau. It would be helpful if the hotel inform you ahead of arrival as to where you are allocated as we had a transfer from the airport and then had to walk over to the other hotel. It is only a few minutes but it’s not the perfect start when you have a lot of luggage or kids or when the weather is bad etc. Wills was extremely helpful, took our bags and walked us over.

We were allocated Balzac room which is right at the front of the hotel on ground level. The room is very small even by Paris standards but we knew we would only be sleeping in the room so it didn’t really matter although storage was a bit of a challenge. As a light sleeper I was worried about noise from the street however I didn’t have any issue with this and didn’t find it noisy at all. The room had cooking facilities along with a kettle and coffee machine which was handy. Nuxe toiletries were provided in the bathroom along with a hair dryer. The hotel provides free Wi-Fi with individual access codes and the connection was really good.

One of the main benefits of this hotel is the location however I’d say the most important thing is the service from the staff which is the best I’ve ever received after many many trips to Paris. Ines couldn’t have been more helpful, making sure we took care when out and about and looking after us all the time.

It’s not a typical hotel, it’s more friendly and has a very homely feel with the informal reception area. There’s nothing worse than having to wait in a long queue to check in or out or to speak to someone on reception if you need something. We didn’t have to wait for anything and the staff would ask if everything was ok every time we were coming or going.

I’d definitely recommend this hotel and look forward to returning soon.

I have been to paris for 5 days
And i choose to stay at helzear
I got the big room with mini kitchen
Staff is very helpful
Room is veryyy clean
Mate clean room everyday
And the location is 5 mins walk to champ elysee
All above is the reasons I recommend this hotel :)

The location is great. Most tourist places are walkable distance .

The staff was very helpful. We stayed only for one night but it was great.

Then hotel upgraded our room which was a welcome surprise . Would recommend the hotel .

I went to Paris for 8 nights, and although the room was smaller than initially expected, it had all the amenities and was ideal due to its prime location. The receptionists were extremely nice and helpful. I would recommend this hotel to anyone looking for a convenient place to stay.

Guys at the front desk were great. Bathroom was of course Euro small but clean. The problem was the noise from Marceau street in front was so loud we literally thought we were on the street trying to sleep even though we were on the 5th floor.

We had a wonderful stay. Even during a hot week of August, it was wonderful to arrive to an air conditioned, cool, impeccable, well decorated apartment.
All the staff were extremely helpful and polite, Khalil in particular. We will definitely go back!

We were travelling as a family of two adults one child and got a spacious two bedroom combo, well equipped, good beds. Housekeeping came by every day. Location is really good, right off the Champs Elysees and easy to get to the city centre by metro and bus which are close by. But still quiet, and next to no traffic (we lived in the apartment building on Rue Chr. Colombe, recommended) Many good restaurants in walking distance. Will definitely come back.

We really enjoyed our stay at Helzear as the location is perfect to see a lots of interesting thing by a short walk. The appartement style room was perfect with kids as we could have a little privacy when they were asleep. The best thing about this hotel is their staff! So helpful and always present to help. It’s our new place now in Paris!

Very nice. Hotel, the. staff was very helpul in all ways.
The location is just amazing 5 to champs Élysées & 10. to the E.tower.

I was satisfied by the service
I'll come back for sure.

(Thank you Halil)

We have stayed here for the second time and will be definitely back next time! The location is perfect and clean and the people are very helpful, interested and friendly. Although the rooms are small, there's anything you need. And most of the time you are outside to visit Paris so there is no complaining. We can really recommend this place!

Beautiful hotel, but it is not like a regular hotel, looks more like an apartment building, very simple but charming and neat. The location is great on Champs-Elysees Ave, just a couple of blocks from Arc de Triomphe. Definitely recommend!

We had a 2 bedroom suite. It was very small, but reasonable by Paris standards. The kitchenette was well stocked and very handy.
The location was perfect with a 10 minute walk to Eiffel Tower and 5 minute walk to Champs-Elysses
The room was clean and comfortable.
Would stay there again

I booked 6 nights at this hotel for 2 adults and 2 kids through Travelocity and paid for it by the time we arrived in Paris.
I chose this hotel based on the location (close to George V, 5 min walking distance) and how their 1 bedroom suite looked on their website. We arrived at 1pm from the airport but we were informed the room was not ready, so we left our luggage and walked around Champs Elysee and grabbed lunch. We came back after 3pm, and we still had to wait another 15 min in their tiny waiting area for our room to be ready.
We were given the Victor Hugo room on the 4th floor. It was tiny, the bedroom fit one king bed and nothing else. There were no bedside table, no chairs, no closet in the room. The picture on the website shows a bed, yellow chair, and coffee table, and bookshelf with ample space to walk around the bed, but the bedroom we were given didn't have any of that except the bed. I felt bad for the maid who made our bed as there were no space between the bed and walls. The curtain in the room do not close properly so the outside light streams through at night. The bathroom is through the bedroom, which was updated and modern.
When you enter the 'suite', there is a built in closet with 5 hangers. The living room had a loveseat sofa bed, once opened it touches the walls on both side, no space to walk around it. The sofa bed was uncomfortable and the springs made noise every time one rolled over. Tiny coffee table, which became a liability once you open the sofa bed, as there aren't too much space to move the coffee table around. There were no other chairs in the whole suite except for the sofa bed. There were no phone or alarm clock in the suite.
The kitchen consisted of 2 burner electric stove, with a mini fridge underneath. The night light under the kitchen vent hood wouldn't turn off (no switch to turn it off), the first night we had to sleep with the light one. The next day, my husband loosened the light bulb so that we can sleep.
We were given 4 flat tiny pillows. I asked for extra pillows and finally received 2 more at the end of the 2nd day.
I requested a bigger room for 3 days in a row, but was told it wasn't available. This is a very small hotel (the 4th floor had 3 units) there were 5 or 6 floors. The main area is a joke, the check in area is small study desk. Nothing about this hotel screams 4 star. I don't know how they have 4 stars. This is barely a 3 star hotel. We received one key (no electronic key card).
As for the amenities at this hotel...the toiletteries are minimal. We kept running out of toilet paper each night as we are only left with half an additional roll. The first day we were given face wash towels, but never replaced after that.
The road is noisy even at night time. There is atleast one police car with sirens go by each night. There are homeless people on the road outside who seem to go through the recycle bottle trash can outside.
I am not sure if the hotel is smoke free or if I was smelling from outside.
Our highlight from staying here is eating at Pret a Manger every morning, and dinner at Italian Restaurant Villa Sophia a block away. We walked to the subway George V (5min) to get around by Metro.
Originally I planned on to return for 2 days at the end of my trip in the same hotel after visiting other countries. But after my bad experience of staying there the first time around, I cancelled the second leg at this hotel and booked into Hotel Residence Foch, which is rated a 3 star hotel, but it is a far superior hotel compared to this place.

I would say this hotel is a good 2 star rating hotel, and with a bit of stretch 3 star hotel. But definitely not a 4 star hotel.
